    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Those who study the fundamental nature of reality, including such concepts as being, substance, essence, time, space, cause, and identity; refers especially to those who create or develop metaphysical theories.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000099620/Legacy AAT data</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Aquellos que estudian la naturaleza fundamental de la realidad, incluyendo conceptos como ser, substancia, esencia, tiempo, espacio, causa e identidad; se refiere especialmente a aquellos que crean o desarrollan teorías metafísicas.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Spanish</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000131/CDBP-SNPC</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000051034/TAA database (2000-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Personen die de fundamentele aard van de realiteit bestuderen. Het betreft concepten zoals het zijn, materie, tijd, ruimte, oorzaak en identiteit. De term heeft vooral betrekking op degenen die metafysische theorieën opstellen of ontwikkelen.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000113770/AAT-Ned (1994-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>對實在的基本要素進行研究的人員，研究主題包括存有、實質、本質、時間、空間、因由和本體等概念；特別指開創或發展出形而上理論的人員。</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
